# The DirectionalLight node defines a light source that illuminates along rays parallel to a given 3-dimensional vector.
# A DirectionalLight node is well-suited to model sunlight, for example.
# If you want to model a light bulb you should rather use a PointLight or a SpotLight node.

DirectionalLight {
  vrmlField SFFloat ambientIntensity 0
  vrmlField SFColor color            1 1 1
  vrmlField SFVec3f direction        0 0 -1
  vrmlField SFFloat intensity        1
  vrmlField SFBool  on               TRUE
  field     SFBool  castShadows      FALSE
  field     SFBool  castLensFlares   FALSE
}
